V!Vanderbilt conduct policies\u000a!!!!Vanderbilt policies apply abroad as well as on campus\u000a<<if $vanderbilt or $facultyled>>Your <span title="The faculty leader is the instructor in charge of your course. There may be more than one faculty leader, and there may also be additional staff to whom they might delegate certain responsibilities.">faculty leader</span> or resident director has sole discretion over all discipline decisions. They will hold you accountable for the standards of behavior described in the VU [[Student Handbook|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/]] and [[Honor System|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/the-honor-system/]], and they may also dictate other rules and guidelines as needed. Your on-site Vanderbilt authority may impose any disciplinary sanction, up to and including dismissal from the program. If you are sanctioned abroad, please note that you also may face further consequences when you return to Vanderbilt.<<else>>You are subject to your abroad institution's rules, but you //also// need to abide by Vanderbilt's conduct policies. The standards of behavior described in the VU [[Student Handbook|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/]] and [[Honor System|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/the-honor-system/]] remain in effect while you are abroad. Conduct that violates these codes may result in sanctions when you return to Vanderbilt, //even if you have already received sanctions from your program abroad.//<</if>>\u000a\u000a''Be sure to read the section in the Student Handbook on'' [[conduct in study abroad programs|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/student-conduct/#conduct-in-study-abroad-programs]].\u000a\u000a<<segue "Vanderbilt policy on alcohol abroad">>\u005c
