V!Student status and billing\u000a!!!!You remain a Vanderbilt student while abroad!\u000aWhile studying abroad, you remain registered as a Vanderbilt student and you retain access to campus resources. You can register for the next term's classes, log in to YES and other applications, utilize safety resources, and make use of campus services, including online library resources.\u000a\u000a<<if not $facultyled>>To make this possible, GEO enrolls you in a study abroad &ldquo;''placeholder course''&rdquo;<<if $summer>> equal to the number of credits you are expected to earn<</if>>. The placeholder will appear on your YES account before you go abroad.<<if $summer>> The actual courses you take abroad, as well as the grades you earn, will eventually replace the placeholder.<<else>> The actual courses you take abroad, as well as the grades you earn, will appear on your transcript under the Study Abroad/Away Credit section.<</if>> This will occur only after your <span title="The official academic record from the term(s) you spent abroad.">transcript</span> arrives from abroad and the University Registrar has processed it. ''It may take 2 to 6 months'' from the end of your program for your transcript to arrive, depending on program and individual circumstances.\u000a\u000a<</if>>''Billing'' works just as it does for on-campus students. [[Vanderbilt Student Accounts|https://finance.vanderbilt.edu/stuaccts/]] will bill you, and your bill will <<if $summer or $maymester>>usually arrive on May 1 or June 1, with the usual payment terms.<<else>>arrive at the same time as usual, with the same payment terms.<</if>> <<if not $facultyled>>You can find estimated fees and other costs in GEO's [[Budget Sheet|https://vanderbilt.edu/geo/finances/budget-sheets/]] for your program. <</if>>Be aware that there are <span title="Costs that are not billed through Vanderbilt--you pay them directly to your study abroad provider or to third parties">''out-of-pocket costs''</span> that are not billed by Vanderbilt--including airfare, visa fees, and more--which you should factor into your overall budget. Contact your <<if $facultyled>>faculty leader<<else>>program provider or GEO advisor<</if>> for more information.\u000a\u000a|box|k\u000a|!What's in my bill?|\u000a|Vanderbilt Tuition<<if ($summer)>>, billed per credit hour<</if>>|\u000a|Program Fee|\u000a|Study Abroad Administrative Fee|\u000a|<hr />//More information:// <<if $maymester>>[[A&S Maymester fee and billing information|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/summer/maysession/abroad-listings.php]]<<else>>[[Billing policies and procedures|https://vanderbilt.edu/geo/finances/costs/]]<</if>>|\u000a\u000a<<sidebar-box "More info">>\u000a	[[Financial aid|Financial aid]]\u000a    [[Maintaining eligibility to study abroad|Maintaining eligibility]]\u000a    [[Withdrawal from a study abroad program|Program withdrawal]]\u000a<</sidebar-box>>\u000a<<segue "Vanderbilt Incident Response for Travel">>\u005c
