V!Grades and Credits\u000a!!!!This is what it's all about, folks\u000a<<if $facultyled>>The course (or courses) you are taking abroad is a Vanderbilt course and earns regular Vanderbilt credit. You will be registered into the course by the college offering the course, usually before you leave campus.\u000a<<elseif $vanderbilt>>You will register for courses when you arrive at your Vanderbilt center abroad. Courses taken at the center are regular Vanderbilt courses and may fulfill any appropriate VU academic requirement.<<elseif $summer>> Courses taken abroad during Summer 2019 will earn Vanderbilt direct credit, and will need to be approved through the [[Study Abroad Course Review process|http://registrar.vanderbilt.edu/study-abroad-course-review/]]; such courses will //not// fulfill <span title="AXLE is the acronym for Achieving Excellence in Liberal Education. It is the core curriculum that all students in the College of Arts and Science must fulfill.">AXLE requirements</span>. Direct Vanderbilt credit otherwise appears on your transcript as if it were taken at Vanderbilt, and it counts toward your Vanderbilt GPA.\u000a<<elseif (not $vanderbilt)>>Courses you take on programs offered through GEO earn Vanderbilt ''Study Abroad/Away Credit''. Study Abroad/Away Credit does not count toward Transfer Credit limits, and you are considered to be "in residency" at Vanderbilt while earning this credit abroad. Your grades will appear on your Vanderbilt transcript (in the Study Abroad/Away Credit section), but will ''not'' count toward your Vanderbilt GPA. Courses taken on GEO programs can count toward majors and minors, or as hours toward graduation. However, individual courses //do not// count toward <span title="AXLE is the acronym for Achieving Excellence in Liberal Education. It is the core curriculum that all students in the College of Arts and Science must fulfill.">AXLE requirements</span>.\u000a<</if>>\u000a<<if (not $summer) and (not $maymester)>>Just as at Vanderbilt, you must take the equivalent of 12-18 hours of credit. <</if>><<if not $facultyled>>Study abroad courses<<if $vanderbilt>> not offered at a Vanderbilt center<</if>> also come with some special rules:\u000a#You may not take courses pass/fail. \u000a#You cannot retake classes abroad that you have already taken on campus (and vice versa). If you do take a course abroad that is equivalent to a course you've already taken on campus, you may get //no credit// for it!\u000a#You cannot opt out of credit for a course you took abroad: all of the credit on your foreign transcript must be recorded at Vanderbilt. Withdraw from courses you don't want to take during the drop/add period!\u000a#Vanderbilt cannot change any grades you earned abroad. If a grade is incorrect, you will need to work with your program provider abroad to get it changed and to issue a new transcript.\u000a#//You// are responsible for monitoring prerequisites and other requirements for courses you take abroad. Consult with your VU academic advisor, but understand that ultimately you are responsible for taking appropriate courses abroad!\u000a#If you are taking a course abroad that will serve as a prerequisite for a course that you'll take when you return to campus, the prerequisite will likely not be on your transcript when you register for VU classes. You will need to contact the Vanderbilt department or instructor offering the course and get written permission to enroll without the abroad prerequisite on your transcript.\u000a\u000a<</if>><<sidebar-box "Academics Abroad">>\u000a	[[How do academic systems abroad differ from Vanderbilt?|Academic systems abroad]]\u000a<</sidebar-box>>\u000a\u000a<<segue "Study abroad course review">>\u005c
