V!Medical Insurance\u000a!!!!You are covered by international insurance\u000aVanderbilt will automatically enroll you in [[Vanderbilt's international travel insurance|https://geo.vanderbilt.edu/_customtags/ct_FileRetrieve.cfm?File_ID=2361]]. This plan is more comprehensive than most plans and includes coverage for mandatory evacuation, preexisting conditions, and mental health and substance abuse treatment. Unlike many international insurance plans, it also covers injuries that involve substance use.\u000a''Before you travel, you will receive an email from our insurance provider'', GeoBlue, with a letter and an insurance card that you can print and carry with you.\u000a\u000aYou may also be enrolled in an international health insurance by your program provider. Be sure to read your insurance benefits for all plans and know how to access health care providers in your host country. ''Know what your insurance covers'' and how to file and pay claims.\u000a\u000a''This insurance only covers you outside the United States.'' GEO strongly encourages all students to maintain health insurance in their home country. If unforeseen circumstances force you to return home, you will want to be insured.\u000a\u000aInternational health insurance usually ''only covers you for the official dates of your program.'' If you are planning to travel before or after your program begins, GEO recommends that you purchase additional short-term coverage. You are free to select any provider, but Vanderbilt's international insurance provider, [[GeoBlue|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/global/health-safety/#insurance]], is readily available at reasonable prices. \u000a\u000aIf you are currently under medical care, your international health insurance can help in locating an appropriate care provider in your host country. Plan ahead!  If you know you want to continue care overseas, contact your international insurance //before// you leave the US.\u000a\u000a|box|k\u000a|!Resources|\u000a|[[Vanderbilt's Office of Global Safety|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/global/global-safety/]], for personal guidance on international insurance, health and wellness, and safety for all travelers|\u000a|[[Medical Care and Insurance|http://www.studentsabroad.com/handbook/medical-care-and-insurance.php?country=General]], a brief guide|\u000a|[[Brief Plan Info for GeoBlue International Health Insurance|https://geo.vanderbilt.edu/_customtags/ct_FileRetrieve.cfm?File_ID=2361]]: This is a basic description of your GeoBlue plan. You may contact GeoBlue for more information on particulars.|\u000a\u000a<<segue "How to use international health insurance">>\u005c
