V<<sidebar "Going abroad ... again!">>\u000aStudents who return from abroad often feel the need to go abroad again.\u000a\u000aIf you are not graduating and you have room in your academic schedule, you are welcome to ''apply for another GEO study abroad program''--there is no rule that says you can only go once! Or, if you are more strapped for time, consider ''volunteering abroad''. You can go over break either with a student organization such as Alternative Spring Break, or by seeking out an external organization. You may even be able to find funding (ask the Office of Immersion Resources about the [[Nichols Humanitarian Fund|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/nicholsfund/]]).\u000a\u000aOr consider ''graduate studies abroad''. Several universities around the world welcome international students for graduate degrees. Many have more reasonable tuition fees than you will find in the US, yet with comparable educational quality and prestige. It is often possible to apply US federal financial aid toward studies at recognized institutions. Some countries, like the United Kingdom, will even give you a one- or two-year work visa upon completion of an advanced degree in their country.\u000a\u000aAnother option might be ''working or interning abroad'', including teaching English abroad. Visit the [[Career Center|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/career/]] for resources and tips for finding an international job, or consult with our sister office the [[English Language Center|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/elc/]] if you are interested in teaching English overseas.\u000a\u000a<<segue "GEO Photo Contest">>\u005c
