V!Your next steps\u000a!!!!What to do now...\u000aBelow are a few things you may need to take care of right now or in the near future. Students, please be sure to ''go to the next page to register your participation'' in this training before quitting.\u000a<ul class="checklist">\u005c\u000a<li><<if storage.getItem("registration") eq true>><input type="checkbox" disabled="disabled" checked="checked"><<else>><<smartcheckbox "$todo.register">><</if>> ''Register your participation'' in the training on the next page!</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.commit">> Formally ''commit to your program'' to ensure that <<if $facultyled>>your program administration and<<else>>GEO and our<</if>> partners are planning for your departure from campus.</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.passport">> ''Apply for a passport'' if you don't have one or if it will expire less than 6 months //after you return// from abroad. Consider expediting if you are behind schedule.</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.visa">> Check requirements for a <<if $facultyled>>''visa''<<else>>''student visa'' or resident permit<</if>>, and decide when you need to begin applying.</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.vaccinations">> Check on required and recommended ''vaccinations'' with your doctor, the [[CDC|http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/travel]], or the [[Student Health Center's Travel Medicine Clinic|https://medschool.vanderbilt.edu/student-health/travel-medicine]].</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.medical">> Get ''medical and dental checkups'', and talk with your care providers about how any existing medical, dental, or mental health conditions can be managed abroad.</li>\u000a<<if $facultyled and ($maymester or $summer)>><li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.campushousing">> If your program has a Nashville component, arrange for your housing. If you are interested in on-campus housing, contact the [[Office of Housing and Residential Education|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/ResEd/main/contact-us/contact-us/]].</li><</if>>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.ead">> If you have ''accommodations'' with [[Student Access Services|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/student-access/]], have them send a letter explaining these to your <<if $facultyled>>faculty leader<<else>>program advisor<</if>>. If you have other needs, consider communicating those to your <<if $facultyled>>faculty leader<<else>>program advisor<</if>> as well.</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.medications">> Learn the generic or local names of any ''medications'' you take on a regular basis, as well as verify their legal status in your host country.</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.travel">> Once you have purchased your airline tickets, ''register your travel'' with the US Department of State [[Smart Traveler program|https://step.state.gov/step/]] (US citizens only).</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.packing">> Start thinking about ''packing'' and any other logistics. You may want to download GEO's [[travelers checklist|https://geo.vanderbilt.edu/_customtags/ct_FileRetrieve.cfm?File_ID=14068]].</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.housing">> ''Housing:'' Monitor your @vanderbilt.edu address for housing registration information and stay updated concerning the 2020-2021 housing assignment process by reviewing the Guide to the Housing Assignment Process, which will be published and available online prior to January 2020. It is your responsibility to participate in the housing assignment process if you intend to return to Vanderbilt for the fall 2020 semester.</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.cardoffice">> ''Commodore Cash:'' Optional: Sign into the Commodore Cash Selection System ([[vanderbi.lt/ccselection|http://vanderbi.lt/ccselection]]) and select \u201c$0\u201d for the semester you will be abroad. Note that any funds you\u2019ve selected will roll over, remaining on your card for the semester you return.</li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.dining">> ''Dining:'' You do not need to take any action at this time. By default you will not receive a meal plan for Spring 2020. For questions or if your plans change, please contact [[meals@vanderbilt.edu|mailto:meals@vanderbilt.edu]]. //While abroad,// monitor your @vanderbilt.edu address for information about upgrading your Fall 2020 meal plan. This is when you will have the opportunity to upgrade your default Fall 2020 meal plan if you wish, or purchase additional flex meals. </li>\u000a<li><<smartcheckbox "$todo.contactinfo">> Scan or photocopy your critical documents (such as passport and credit cards), and create an [[emergency contact information card|$emergencyCardURL]] to carry with you.</li></ul>\u000aRemember, if you have questions about your next steps or any other aspect of your study abroad experience, GEO staff are standing by! [[Contact us|https://vanderbilt.edu/geo/advising/]].\u000a\u000a<<segue "Register your participation">>\u005c
