V<div><img src="images/ePDO logo.png" alt="Study Abroad Predeparture Guide"></div><div><a href="http://vanderbilt.edu/" target="_blank"><img alt="Vanderbilt logo" id="VU-logo" src="images/VU_logo.png"/></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://vanderbilt.edu/geo" target="_blank"><img alt="Global Education Office logo" id="GEO-logo" src="images/GEO.4c.web.png" /></a></div>\u005c\u000a<<if config.historyMode eq HistoryMode.Hash or $browserSupport eq "no">><div class="message-box problem"><span>Your browser (<<print $UAinfo.browser.name>> v<<print $UAinfo.browser.major>> running on <<print $UAinfo.os.name>>) is not supported. We recommend that you either use another browser (see below) or download the [[PDF|$pdfURL]].</span></div>\u005c\u000a<<elseif $browserSupport eq "unknown">><div class="message-box warning"><span>Your browser (<<print $UAinfo.browser.name>> v<<print $UAinfo.browser.major>> running on <<print $UAinfo.os.name>>) may not work well for this training module. We recommend that you try another browser instead (see below). You may also download the [[PDF|$pdfURL]].</span></div><</if>>\u005c\u000a\u000aThe Global Education Office welcomes you to our ''Study Abroad Predeparture Guide''. The training modules within introduce you to a wealth of information--information that you will need to have a successful and safe experience abroad. Please read everything carefully.\u000a\u000aYou can take the ''Quick Tour'' now for a very brief introduction to the Training interface. It will quickly show you what all of the elements on this page are and what they do. <<button "Take the Tour">><<script>>ga('send', 'event', 'help', 'tour', 'launched tour from intro page'); activateHelp();<</script>><</button>>\u000a\u000aFrom time to time, you will see a red box like the one below that provides ''In-Depth Information'' on a topic or topics. We recommend that you read these links in all cases where a topic could conceivably apply to you! Just click on the red links to check them out.\u000a\u000a<<sidebar-box "In-Depth Information">>\u000a   [[Click here for a sample, just to see how it works!|Sample]]\u000a<</sidebar-box>>\u005c\u000a\u000aThroughout the training, ''blue hyperlinks'' will direct you to external sites with useful information or further resources. For example, this link will take you to the [[Global Education Office's home page|http://vanderbilt.edu/geo]].\u000a\u000aWhen you're ready to move on, hit the ''big blue Continue button'' at the bottom of the page!\u000a\u000a!!!!!Browser support\u000aThis presentation works best with recent versions of the major <span title="The application you use to access and view websites is called a web browser.">web browsers</span> on desktops, tablets, and smartphones. If you are having trouble with the presentation, try upgrading your web browser. Or you may [[download the presentation in PDF format|$pdfURL]] instead.\u000a\u000a<<display "Browsers">>\u005c\u000a\u000a<<segue "What you will get out of study abroad">>\u000a\u000a//Edition: <<print $edition>>//\u000a/% !!!!Choose mode to continue\u000aThis presentation can be viewed in Automatic Mode, with a narrator speaking the text, or in Manual Mode. You can turn Automatic Mode on or off at any time using the button in the upper right.\u000a\u000aYou can always hit the <span class='continue-button' style="clear:both;"><<click "Continue" $first>><<set options.autoplay to true>><<updateAutoplay>><<saveoptions>><</click>><span class="anim-wrapper"><span class='onward-arrow fade-bounce'>&raquo;</span></span>&ensp;</span> button at any time to advance.\u000a\u000a<<click "Continue in Automatic Mode" $first>>\u005c\u000a    <<set options.autoplay to true>>\u005c\u000a    <<updateAutoplay>>\u005c\u000a    <<saveoptions>>\u005c\u000a<</click>>\u000a<<click "Continue in Manual Mode" $first>>\u005c\u000a    <<set options.autoplay to false>>\u005c\u000a    <<updateAutoplay>>\u005c\u000a    <<saveoptions>>\u005c\u000a<</click>>\u005c\u000a<<stopAllSounds>>\u005c\u000a<<set options.autoplaydelay to 1000 >>\u005c\u000a<<saveoptions>>\u005c\u000a%/\u005c
