V<img alt="Yellow warning symbol--pay attention!" src="images/warning.png" class="left inline" style="width:40px; margin-right:10px;" />\u005c\u000a!Passport Check\u000a!!!!Be sure that you have a valid passport, and that it will not be expiring within the next year or so.\u000aBefore we go any further, take a moment to check your passport's expiration date.\u000a\u000a<<figure "images/passport_expiration.jpg" "Where to find the expiration date on your main passport page." "" "Photo showing location of expiration date on the main passport information page. It is located toward the bottom of the passport page.">>Most countries will not allow you <<if $facultyled or $shortterm>>to get a student visa or residence permit<<else>>to enter<</if>> if your passport is near its expiration date. ''Be sure that your passport does not expire until at least 6 months after your program ends!''\u000a\u000a|box|k\u000a|!COVID Considerations|\u000a|For reasons related to COVID-19, [[processing times|https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/passports/how-apply/processing-times.html]] for US passports are longer than usual. If you will need a new passport to study abroad and have not yet begun the process of applying, ''contact your GEO advisor immediately!''|\u000a\u000a<<sidebar-box>>\u000a	[[Uh oh, it looks like I need a new passport!|Getting or renewing a passport]]\u000a<</sidebar-box>>\u000a\u000a|box|k\u000a|!Resources|\u000a|[[US Department of State video on passport requirements|https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yAQdMNqvrxE]]|\u000a\u000a<<segue "Passport and document security">>
