V!Vanderbilt Incident Response for Travel\u000a!!!!Emergency and travel assistance for Vanderbilt students\u000aOne of the services that you have access to while abroad is Vanderbilt Incident Response for Travel (VIRT).\u000a\u000aVIRT is a ''round-the-clock team dedicated to providing safety-related assistance'' to members of the Vanderbilt University community who are away from campus on VU-related travel. VIRT works to implement cross-campus procedures to ensure an effective and consistent response to any VU travel emergency.\u000a\u000aYou can contact VIRT for assistance with many types of issues. Some examples include:\u000a*Connecting you with appropriate health care abroad\u000a*Providing medical consultation to help you make informed decisions\u000a*Guiding you in using Vanderbilt-issued insurance\u000a*Coordinating a medical or emergency evacuation from abroad\u000aIn an emergency, you can call VIRT at ''+1 615-322-2745'' any time of the day or night, any day of the year. Tell the VU Public Safety dispatcher that you want to report an issue to VIRT.\u000a\u000aYou can also contact VIRT <a href="mailto:virt@vanderbilt.edu">via email</a> if you are not facing an emergency. A response will come within 24 hours.\u000a\u000aPlease take a moment now to ''enter the following contact information'' into your cell phone's address book:\u000a\u000a<<display "VIRT contact info">>\u005c\u000a\u000aIf you prefer paper, you can print and carry GEO's [[wallet-sized emergency numbers directory|$emergencyCardURL]].\u000a\u000aVIRT coordinates with campus offices to support VU travelers. These offices include, but are not limited to, the Office of Global Safety, Student Health Center, the University Counseling Center, Student Access Services, Title IX & Student Discrimination, the Global Education Office, Project Safe, and Risk & Insurance Management.\u000a\u000a<<segue "Emergency contact and notifications">>\u005c
