V!Sexual misconduct abroad\u000a!!!!Regardless of local law, Vanderbilt policies apply\u000aSocial norms--and civil and criminal laws--vary from country to country.  Even so, Vanderbilt\u2019s policies, including the university\u2019s Student Accountability and Sexual Misconduct and Intimate Partner Violence policies, apply in all study abroad programs in which Vanderbilt students participate, whether those programs are administered by Vanderbilt or a third party.  Vanderbilt students, faculty and staff participating in study abroad programs must comply with local laws, the rules and regulations of their study abroad program, and with Vanderbilt\u2019s policies.\u000a\u000aIf you are a victim of sexual misconduct while abroad, contact the <<if $facultyled>>faculty leader<<else>>resident director<</if>> of your program for help. If you are unable or unwilling to discuss the issue with program staff, please contact [[Vanderbilt Incident Response for Travel (VIRT)|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/virt/]], Vanderbilt's [[Title IX Office|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/title-ix/]] or [[Project Safe|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/projectsafe/]]. Project Safe has someone available around the clock every day of the year. The Student Handbook\u2019s [[policy on Sexual Misconduct|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/sexual-misconduct/]] identifies confidential resources (see also [[Project Safe|https://cdn.vanderbilt.edu/vu-wp0/wp-content/uploads/sites/133/2013/11/11204527/Resource_List_2020_2021.pdf]]).\u000a\u000aNot all countries offer the same legal protections for victims as are offered in the United States. Again, Vanderbilt can explain your options ''before you file a formal police report''. Contact VIRT/Office of Global Safety, Title IX, or Project Safe; the Student Handbook\u2019s [[policy on Sexual Misconduct|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/sexual-misconduct/]] identifies confidential resources (see also [[Project Safe|https://cdn.vanderbilt.edu/vu-wp0/wp-content/uploads/sites/133/2013/11/11204527/Resource_List_2020_2021.pdf]]).\u000a\u000aThe range of sanctions for violations of Vanderbilt\u2019s Student Accountability and Sexual Misconduct and Intimate Partner Violence Policies are set forth in the Student Handbook. Individuals who engage in gender-based or sexual misconduct--or other forms of misconduct--may also be subject to local laws, and the civil and criminal consequences may be severe.\u000a\u000a|box|k\u000a|!Resources|\u000a|[[VU Student Accountability Policy|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/student-conduct/]], from the Student Handbook|\u000a|[[Sexual Misconduct and Intimate Partner Violence Policy|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/student_handbook/sexual-misconduct/]], from the Student Handbook|\u000a|[[Vanderbilt Incident Response for Travel (VIRT)|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/virt/]]|\u000a|[[VU Title IX Office|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/title-ix/]]|\u000a|[[VU Project Safe|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/projectsafe/]] will research local resources when a student needs in-person advocacy or support, wherever they are--including abroad.|\u000a|[[Vanderbilt Sexual Assault Support and Resources List|https://cdn.vanderbilt.edu/vu-wp0/wp-content/uploads/sites/133/2013/11/11204527/Resource_List_2020_2021.pdf]]|\u000a\u000a<<segue "Grades and credits">>\u005c
