V<<sidebar "Withdrawing from your program">>\u000aWe hope you won't have to withdraw from your program. But if you must, please note the following:\u000a\u000a<<if $vanderbilt>>|box|k\u000a|!Withdrawal Deadline|<<if $maymester>>You need to withdraw by the Withdrawal Deadline specified on the [[Maymester/Summer Sessions page|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/summer/maysession/abroad-listings.php]]<<else>>In your GEO account ([[log in|https://geo.vanderbilt.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Security.ExistingUserLogin]]), you will find a Withdrawal Deadline. You need to withdraw by this date<</if>> to avoid penalties.|\u000a|!Communication|You must withdraw with GEO in writing.<<if $facultyled>> Be sure to also notify your course instructor/faculty leader.<</if>>|\u000a|!Potential Costs|If you withdraw after the stated Withdrawal Deadline, <<if $maymester>>the VU college offering the course<<else>>GEO<</if>> may bill a monetary penalty to your VU student account. Such penalties generally increase as the departure date gets closer. If you must withdraw, do so as early as you can!|<<else>>|box|k\u000a|!Obligations|If you signed an agreement with one of our partners (CIEE, CET, IFSA, etc.), you will owe them directly. GEO will generally bill such a fee via your student account.|\u000a|!Communication|You must withdraw with GEO in writing. If you applied to one of Vanderbilt's partner organizations (e.g., CIEE, CET, IFSA), you must contact //both// the partner and GEO to communicate your decision.|\u000a|!Potential Costs|If you withdraw after the stated Withdrawal Deadline or after committing to attend, our partner may bill a monetary penalty to your VU student account. Such penalties generally increase as the departure date gets closer. If you must withdraw, do so as early as you can!|\u000a|!COVID-19|Many partners have adopted more flexible COVID-19 withdrawal policies. If you are uncertain what your program's policies are, check in with your [[GEO advisor|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/geo/advising/]].|<</if>>\u005c\u000a\u000a<<if $maymester>>Please read the full [[Maymester Withdrawal policy|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/summer/maysession/abroad-listings.php]]<<else>>Please read GEO's full [[Withdrawal Instructions and Policies|https://vanderbilt.edu/geo/advising/policies/#withdrawal]]<</if>>.\u000a\u000a<<segue "Preparation and responsibilities">>\u005c
