V<<sidebar "Career resources while abroad">>\u000aBefore you go abroad, consider [[connecting with a Career Coach|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/career/]] to discuss how studying abroad might benefit and intersect with your job or internship search.\u000a\u000aThe Career Center has many career resources available to you while you are abroad. Start with the [[Information for Students Studying Abroad|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/career/information-for/studyingabroad/]] page to become acquainted with resources and frequently asked questions from students. \u000a\u000aCareer Center resources are available to you while you are abroad. All of the ''Career Center\u2019s coaches are available'' by phone, Zoom, email, and Skype throughout the year to answer your questions and to help you explore and pursue jobs and internships. \u000a\u000aWhile you're abroad, you may want to ''make connections with Vanderbilt alumni'' who work in the countries you're visiting. These networking connections can often lead to opportunities. See the Career Center's [[Information for Students Studying Abroad|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/career/information-for/studyingabroad/]] page for notes on how to do this.\u000a\u000aIf you are ''invited to interview while you are abroad'', reach out and let the company know that you are abroad. Ask if they would be able to set up a Zoom, Skype, or phone interview with you instead. If you found the job through DoreWays and you cannot find the contact information for the company, email [[recruiting@vanderbilt.edu|mailto:recruiting@vanderbilt.edu]] for assistance. Remember the time difference of your country when contacting them and scheduling interviews.\u000a\u000aPlease contact the Career Center with any questions. They are here to support you!\u000a\u000a|box|k\u000a|!Contact the Career Center|\u000a|Phone: 615-322-2750|\u000a|Email: [[careercenter@vanderbilt.edu|mailto:careercenter@vanderbilt.edu]]|\u000a|Website: [[www.vanderbilt.edu/career|http://www.vanderbilt.edu/career]]|\u000a\u000a<<segue "Conduct and law">>\u005c
