V!Emergency contact and parent/guardian notifications\u000a!!!!When do we contact your family?\u000a\u000aAs a part of your GEO application, you have provided ''emergency contact information'' and (optionally) ''parent/guardian contact information''. \u000a\u000aGEO will notify your ''emergency contact'' in the following cases:\u000a*You are unable to speak for yourself\u000a*You have been missing for more than 24 hours\u000a*You are perceived to be a danger to yourself or others\u000a*There is a significant health, safety, or security incident affecting your study abroad program (e.g. civil unrest, mass violence, extreme weather, etc.)\u000aGEO will use the ''parent/guardian contact information'' to provide information about your study abroad experience (e.g. billing) in advance of your program's start date. The parent/guardian contact information form will ''not'' be used in the event of a real or perceived emergency. \u000a\u000a<<segue "Preparation and responsibilities">>\u005c
