V!Getting there (and back again)\u000a!!!!Considerations around planning your trip\u000aWith the coronavirus epidemic still impacting travel worldwide, there are a number of realities and possibilities to keep in mind.\u000a\u000aGEO recommends you purchase a ''flexible class of airline ticket'' that allows for itinerary changes at minimal cost. Given ever-shifting coronavirus precautions and entry/exit requirements, ''simpler itineraries are preferred''.\u000a\u000aRequirements are changing rapidly, but when you arrive in your host country, you ''//may// be required to quarantine''. If so, this quarantine is likely to be stricter than the self-isolation requirements you may have encountered in the US in the early days of the pandemic. For example, you likely would not be able to receive guests or go outside. If a quarantine looks likely when you travel, we strongly encourage you to think about what you can do to avoid boredom and support your mental health. Here is a [[helpful list of guidelines|https://iocdf.org/covid19/self-care-during-covid-19/]] to get you started.\u000a\u000aRequirements and restrictions imposed by the US government, foreign governments, regional governments, airlines, or other entities may change at any time. ''You are ultimately responsible'' for being aware of and taking action to ensure that you meet all these requirements.\u000a\u000aCurrently, all travelers\u2014regardless of vaccination status\u2014will need to show a negative COVID-19 test result (or proof of recovery from COVID) to [[return to the United States|https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/international-travel/before-you-go/covid-19_testing_required_US_Entry.html]]. Your program will likely help you arrange for this testing. However, if you plan to travel independently after your program, be sure that you will be in a location where you can take a test of the correct type in the days prior to departure, verify that it can be completed as quickly as you need it to be, make an appointment for that test as needed, and ensure you have funds available to pay for the test. To review the type of test and documentation you\u2019ll need, see the [[CDC\u2019s guidelines|https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/pdf/Airline_Testing_Order_Checklist-p.pdf]]. Be aware that ''airlines interpret CDC rules and that you should check with your airline as to what constitutes sufficient proof''\u2014including the language(s) that documentation may be submitted in. See the [[CDC\u2019s website|https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/travelers/testing-international-air-travelers.html]] for more information.\u000a\u000aIf you need to ''travel on an emergency basis'' while you are abroad, that is unlikely to happen immediately. Due to the (current) need to show a negative test result before traveling to the US, as well as other regulations and requirements, you should not plan on being able to leave within a window of less than 48 hours. For example, if there is a family emergency and you need to return home to the US, you will not be able to do so immediately. If your family lives outside the US, you might want to research and keep up with the requirements you need to fulfill to return to your home country.\u000a\u000aGEO generally recommends that you consider supplemental insurance to cover your entire time abroad. ''Trip cancellation/trip interruption'' and ''theft insurance'' are particularly worthwhile options. GEO cannot recommend specific  plans or providers, but you can check with your travel agent, home/auto  insurance agent, or online. During COVID-19, decisions about trip interruption insurance may be more complicated; if you are considering this option, the [[Office of Global Safety|https://www.vanderbilt.edu/global/global-safety/]] would be happy to consult with you.\u000a\u000a<<sidebar-box>>\u000a   [[How do I go about getting a travel visa?|How to get a travel visa]]\u000a   [[Can I arrive early or leave late from my study abroad site?|Early arrivals]]\u000a   [[What about traveling with a musical instrument?|Traveling with a musical instrument]]\u000a<</sidebar-box>>\u000a\u000a<<segue "Passport Check">>\u005c
